# Tungsten — whole-stage codegen

## Catalyst plans it, Tungsten runs it fast

- **Off-heap memory** — structured binary buffers *outside* the JVM heap → bypass the garbage collector, cache-friendlier layout
- **Whole-stage code generation** — one fused JVM method per stage pushes a row through every operator at once (filter → project → aggregate)
  - **One loop**, not one call per operator per row

## Why DataFrames beat RDDs

- An RDD has **no schema** — Tungsten can't lay it out or generate stage code
- A DataFrame's schema is a **contract Tungsten compiles against**
- Proof in the plan: operators wrapped in **`*(N) WholeStageCodegen`**
